# Rust
target/
target
/target
**/*.rs.bk
# Cargo.lock is committed (Rust convention for binary-shipping
# workspaces: guarantees reproducible builds + the Docker install
# path's `COPY Cargo.toml Cargo.lock ./` requires it in the build
# context).

# Node
node_modules/
dist/
.next/
*.tsbuildinfo

# Environment
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# IDE
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Claude Code
.claude/

# Build artifacts
*.log

# Playwright artifacts
test-results/
playwright-report/

# TLA+ tooling — downloaded on demand by infra/tla/run-tlc.sh
infra/tla/tla2tools.jar
# TLC writes states/ alongside the spec when checking; .toolbox/
# is the IDE state from the official TLA+ Toolbox.
docs/formal/states/
docs/formal/*.toolbox/
**/__pycache__/

# Generated seed bundles — `infra/postgres/regenerate-brewery-seed.sh`
# rebuilds them from source (JobKinds + tenant.toml + the live sim).
# Don't commit; runtime consumers (bootstrap-local.sh,
# reset-to-baseline.sh, oss-quickstart/init.sh) fetch or regenerate
# as needed. Keeps git history slim and forces every deployment to
# start from a known-fresh artifact rather than a stale snapshot.
infra/postgres/seed-brewery-audit-log.sql.gz
infra/postgres/seed-brewery-audit-log.meta.json
